The evidence with the title 'Cannulated cow - Wikipedia ' says A cannula in a cow's side. A cannulated cow or "fistulated cow" refers to a cow that has been surgically fitted with a cannula . A cannula acts as a porthole-like device that allows access to the rumen of a cow , to perform research and analysis of the digestive system .  ... A window to the world of a cow 's stomach: researchers cannulate cows to  ... 
